The graphics are absolutely stunning, but lose a few points for a quirky frame rate and lack of spectacular lighting, but damn they sure are perdy!
It isn't trying to be competition to the tennis sims, it's providing an alternative option that is simple, easy and fun.
There's no way around it: the game rocks.
As blotchy as it is, it still remains as pure an arcade sports title as you can hope to find.
